parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: the passenger airbag light stays on even when an adult is seated
the airbag light comes on intermittently
the airbag system fails to deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dim headlights can cause reduced visibility while driving at night, increasing the risk of accidents and potentially leading to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: making it difficult to see while driving at night
even with high beams on; fog lights provide better illumination than low beams; bulbs have been replaced multiple times

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can cause accidents and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intention to stop.
symptoms: Brake lights remain on even when the vehicle is turned off
requiring the fuse to be removed to turn them off; brake switch recall started for 2008 models

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sun visor can cause obstructed visibility, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when driving at intersections or stopping at traffic lights.
symptoms: The sun visor fails to stay in the upright position
obstructing the driver's view; the visor cannot be folded up or out of the way; the visor's tension is lost
